column4: Just started using ubuntu on Dell Lattitude D600.  It's a bit slow, but can't get Available Wireless networks to show up on list.

opena  terminal and type "lspci" no quotes, and hit enter(thats a lowercase L)... go throught he list (don't paste the whole freakin list here)... and find your wireless device, and tell us what it is.
i've told you twice... we need to know your device, i told you above how to figure out your device.
